Switching characters detonates the Frozen effect, dealing DMG based on the number of effects stacked.
Recovers Dodge Gauge by 300 after a 3-Ping
Extra DMG bonus increases by X% for 5s after dodging.
Each successful dodge grants a permanent X% Extra DMG bonus, up to Y%. Resets when being hit.
Switching members will fully restore the Dodge Gauge and grant Extra DMG bonus based on the Dodge Gauge for 10s.

Randomizes a number every 15s and gains its effect: 0-24, DMG from Pinging Orbs increases by 30%. 24-49, Signature Move DMG increases by 30%. 50-74, Basic ATK DMG increases by 30%. 75-89, triggers all effects from 0-74. 90-98, DMG dealt decreases by half. 99, reduces the current character's HP by 100% (this DMG is not lethal).
DMG dealt ranges between 80%-140% of the DMG.
The first 3 Destiny after deployed are guaranteed to be buffs, and their effects increase by 50%.

Replaces Destiny effect with a special counter. It randomly adds 1-6 every time you switch a character. Characters are enhanced based on the current number, and the number resets when it is over 21. The counter adds 1 automatically every second. (Switching will reset the +1 timer)
Enters the "Shadow Dance" state after a 3-Ping. Deals 15% of the total DMG dealt after 8s and includes it in the Combo. 15s cooldown. Cooldown is determined separately for each character.

The first time the Combo reaches the following after a character is deployed, the whole team gains the associated effects: 50, the whole team gains 3 Orbs of the same color. 75, gains 30 Energy. 100, deals DMG equal to 500% ATK to all surrounding enemies immediately. 150, the current character gains "Immovable". 200, Extra DMG bonus increases by 50%. Effects cannot be gained twice. Combo resets after switching characters.
Switching characters after a 100-hit Combo will clear it. Clearing a X-hit Combo will increase Extra DMG bonus by Y% up to Z% for 8s. 15s cooldown.
Extra DMG bonus increases by 100% when Combo is lower than 10. The bonus increases by 50% when Combo is lower than 20, and it increases by 20% when the Combo is lower than 30.

Enters "Preparation" state for 5s after a 3-Ping. Dealing DMG in this state will lower the switching cooldown by 0.5s. Effect triggers in 1s intervals. Each trigger refreshes the timer on "Preparation".
Grants 1/3 of the total Orbs Pinged by a character on the battlefield (rounded up) to the next character deployed.
Increases Extra DMG bonus by 15% for 5s after a character enters the battlefield.
The next character entering the battlefield receives a 15%/30%/50% Extra DMG bonus for 5/8/10s if the previous character has dealt a total of 50k/80k/100k DMG.
Enemies activates First-aid when their HP drops to 10%. If they are still alive after 5s, immediately recover 20% HP. 10s cooldown.
Enemy damage also causes Burn for 5s (dealing damage every second).
After clearing this stage, enemies lose 10% HP when they spawn in Deep Hive.
Upon death, the enemy lays a mine under its feet.

Operation Maintenance Area 3 Basic. 30s after the start of battle, 1 laser device will appear to launch 1 laser every 20s at ally units, dealing damage. The laser has its interval reduced by 5s and deals 10% more damage every 60s.
The power laser in Deep Hive has shorter alarm period
Deep Hive now has an additional power laser
After clearing this stage, the power laser enters the battle 30s later in Deep Hive
Operation Maintenance Area 4 Basic. 30s after the start of battle, 2 Jitterbombs will appear. The interval is reduced by 2s each time and more Jitterbombs will appear (up to 4).
Jitterbomb has a 50% chance to cause a dark explosion before death.
Increases the limit time of Deep Hive by 30s after clearing this stage.
Area 6 Week 1 Electrocute: Inflict Lightning DMG equal to 20% ATK upon dealing damage
Area 6 Week 1 Lightning: Generate a vertical or diagonal lightning in turn around the target every 8s
Area 6 Week 1 Dominator: Immune to Maxtrix effects
Area 6 Week 1 Overload: Upon receiving Lightning DMG, lose 200 Dodge and 40 Energy within 4s. The effect can't be stacked.
Area 6 Week 1 Iron Shield: Have a shield equal to 30% max HP upon deployment. The shield will not be refreshed.
Area 6 Week 2 Prime: There will be two more Primes on the field to assist the enemies in battle.
Area 6 Week 2 Drum: The Twin Generals will grant different halos to the enemies when on the field.
Area 6 Week 2 Restart: Upon the death of one of the Twin Generals, both of them will die and revive in 20s.
Area 6 Week 2 Recovery: The Twin Generals will gain the Recovery γ effect and restore 100 HP per second.
Area 6 Week 2 Power: The Twin Generals will gain a 50% Extra DMG Bonus.

Area 6 Week 3 Ascension: There will be an invincible Alpha that can't be selected off-site, who will begin to fire swordwaves at you and your allies 33s after the battle starts. Each time Alpha fires will reduce her firing interval by 3s and increase the swordwave damage by 10%. (10% per second when in the Infinite Swordwave status). Swordwaves +1 every 3 rounds.
Area 6 Week 3 Blade: Base swordwave damage increases by 50%.
Area 6 Week 3 Pursuit: Swordwaves +1 upon first wave fired
Area 6 Week 3 Split: Swordwaves fired will come with 2 hits of smaller swordwaves.
Area 6 Week 3 Grave Wounds: Swordwaves will deal Extra DMG equal to 100% of their damage and reduce healing by 25% within 5s after hitting the target. The effect can be stacked.

Area 6 Perfect Tactics: Upon switch of members, gains permanent 20% Extra DMG Bonus. Can be stacked up to 10 times. Gains a shield equal to 30% max HP and Super Armor within 15s. Both can be stacked up to 2 times.
